Step 1. Calculate Gross Profit Margin.  
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 2610115.02 and Total Revenue = 5695115.02  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (2610115.02 / 5695115.02) × 100  
  ≈ 45.83%

Step 2. Calculate Operating Cash Flow Ratio.  
• From the cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -224133.22  
• From the balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 829755.77  
• Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities  
  = (-224133.22) / 829755.77  
  ≈ -0.27

Thus, in the required JSON format, the solution is:

{"solution": {"Gross Profit Margin": "45.83%", "Operating Cash Flow Ratio": "-0.27"}}
